Dr. Cristina Pattuelli and Matt Miller recently taught an intensive summer school course on <a title="University of Bologna Course Site" href="http://www.beniculturali.unibo.it/it/attivita-didattica/linked-data-per-i-beni-culturali" target="_blank">Linked Open Data for Cultural Heritage</a> at the University of Bologna, Department for Cultural Heritage, Ravenna Campus – May 16-20, 2016. The course focused on the <span class="notranslate">principles and techniques of Linked Data as applied to cultural heritage institutions.</span> Check out the course <a href="https://eventi.unibo.it/linked-data-per-i-beni-culturali">website</a>, including an outline of course topics.

[gallery ids="1208,1207,1206"]

&nbsp;

In an effort to tackle the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_bias_on_Wikipedia">gender bias on Wikipedia</a> and foster jazz appreciation, Linked Jazz hosted a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Meetup/New_Orleans/WomenOfJazz">New Orleans Women of Jazz Wikipedia edit-a-thon</a> at the 8th Annual JEN Conference this January.   Search #WomenofJazz on Twitter to see what fellow Wikipedians contributed!

